cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image segmentation using deep neural networks and leverages weak supervision to improve performance. The paper specifically focuses on medical images, which are often difficult to annotate at the pixel level. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a semi-supervised framework, which involves training with both labeled and unlabeled data, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper uses image-to-image translation, which is a popular technique in generative models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with medical images, which are a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
